bulgogi.html


        
            <p><em>INGREDIENTS</em>\n 
            '1 1/2 lbs boneless rib eye steak'\n 
            '1/2 small pear, peeled and coursely grate'\n
            '1/4 cup reduced sodium soy sauce'\n 
            '2 tablespoons brown sugar'\n 
            '3 cloves of garlic, minced'\n 
            '1 tablespoon freshly grated ginger'\n 
            '1 tablespoon gochujang (Korean red pepper paste)'\n 
            '2 tablespoons vegetable oil, divided'\n 
            '2 green onions, thinly sliced'\n 
            '1 teaspoon toasted sesame seeds'</P>
            
            <p><em>DIRECTIONS</em>\n 
            '1. Wrap steak in plastic wrap, and place in the freezer for 30 minutes. '\n 
            'Unwrap and slice across the grain into 1/4 inch thick slices. '/n
            '2. In a medium bowl, combine pear, soy sauce, ginger and gochjang. '\n 
            'In a gallon size ziploc bag, combine soy suace mixture and steak; '\n
            'marinate at least 2 hours to overnight, turning bag occasionally.'\n 
            '3. Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in cast iron skillet over medium-'\n 
            'to high heat. Working in batches, add steak to the pan in a single layer '\n
            'and cook until charred and cooked through, about 2-3 minutes per side. '\n 
            'Repeat with remaining 1 tablespoon vegetable oil and steak. '\n 
            '4. Serve immediately, garnished with green onions and sesame seeds, if desired.'</p>
</body>
